t kid on the block, but I strongly suspect she would have picked up on some other clues if she was really pregnant.</p><p><em>This shows one big change in the last ten years. No-one cares about Big Brother at all any more. Channel 4 realised that and they very sensibly killed itÂ off a couple of years ago. Channel 5 have been broadcasting it since then. It’s running currently but I couldn’t name one of the housemates. I haven’t seen a single front-page headline about it this year. Of course, there are other reality TV shows that grab the headlines instead. As far as I can see, that’s mainly the talent shows.</em></p><div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"><div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon sd-sharing"><h3 class="sd-title">Share this:</h3><div class="sd-content"><ul><li class="share-twitter"><a class="share-twitter sd-button share-icon no-text" data-shared="sharing-twitter-108" href="/2002/07/big-brother-still-not-news/?share=twitter" onclick="__gaTracker(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;outbound-article&#39;, &#39;http://wasted.dave.org.uk/2002/07/big-brother-still-not-news/?share=twitter&#39;, &#39;Click to share on Twitter (Opens in new window)&#39;);" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="Click to share on Twitter"><span></span><span class="sharing-screen-reader-text">Click to share on Twitter (Opens in new window)</span></a></li><li class="share-facebook"><a class="share-facebook sd-button share-icon no-text" data-shared="sharing-facebook-108" href="http://wasted.dave.org.uk/2002/07/big-brother-still-not-news/?share=facebook" onclick="__gaTracker(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;outbound-article&#39;, &#39;http://wasted.dave.org.uk/2002/07/big-brother-still-not-news/?share=facebook&#39;, &#39;Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window)&#39;);" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="Click to share on Facebook"><span></span><span class="sharing-screen-reader-text">Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window)</span><